THE JOURNEY 🙌🏾 [SWIPE]

To be FREE & HEALTHY!!!! 

I can’t believe 10 years ago I use to be 301lbs. I am so proud of myself on how I’ve been able to keep the weight off for so long. I remember when I made the decision to loose the weight not knowing that eventually living a healthier life would become a LIFESTYLE. 

I told God to change my appetite and help me to crave things that are more healthier for me physically, mentally, emotionally and spiritually. This journey to a healthier me has had its ups and downs. But I am so glad that I stayed the course and never gave up! 

I encourage you to keep going… Keep fighting for your life! And keep fighting for a better you!

-Kalessia K 🥀

TRANSFORMATION TUESDAY💪🏾

If I told you it was easy I would be lying. But what I will say is… 

One of the best decisions I made this year or here in these past few months was to prioritize me. Focus on me and take all the energy I was putting into trying to get someone to love me and started loving on Keke. 

I have always been up and down in my weight. Mostly due too distractions. But once I made the decision to starve my distractions and feed my focus everything around me literally started to change. Including my mindset.

Though I am not at my goal weight, I still strive everyday to work towards becoming a healthier me. 

I am so excited to introduce this new version of me in 2024. She has come a long way and I am extremely proud of her. 🫶🏾✨
Last post of 2023 ✨🫶🏾

I made a decision 3 months into ending out the year 2023 that I would stop sleeping on myself and my potential to be the best version of myself I could possibly be. Not just for the year of 2024, but literally a complete lifestyle change mentally. 

This is my Era of new levels, new beginnings, new me, new lifestyle! 

I encourage you to step out of your comfort zone and try something new this year. Rather if that’s to start the business, write the book, apply for the job, book that therapy session or simply live a new healthier lifestyle. JUST DO IT! It doesn’t have to be perfect… JUST START!!!! 

Trust God and take that leap of Faith into something new. I promise you won’t regret it. ✨🖤

Forever “That Girl” 💅🏽
